  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rehabilitation and Upgrade the damaged houses of Returnees in eastern districts of Aleppo, Syria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through ERF funds, this Shelter Upgrade Project shall assist IDPs by improving the physical conditions of buildings of unfinished complex in Aleppo Governorate. The association will upgrade unfinished buildings in various stages of completion to provide shelter space for newly displaced, improve the living conditions for IDPs already squatting in skeleton buildings and ensure minimum conditions of safety for families, in particular children, often at risk of accidents in these structures. The need for such interventions is expected to increase as the Government continues to implement the policy of evacuating IDPs from collective shelters, such as school buildings, and in particular the university dormitories in Aleppo. The works will be complementary to the available WASH facilities implemented or to be so the IDPs will enjoy a decent and safe shelter. Shelter support will target vulnerable groups such as women-headed households, elderly and people with disabilities. As an overall target, Taalouf in 2016 plans to support up to 3860 IDPs (193 apartments *4families in each apartment *5 Individuals in each family =3860 IDPs) with shelter solutions, subject to availability of funding levels requested.</narrative>
  </description>
